// LLM Phase 2 — transpose_f32: out[N, M] = transpose(in[M, N]).
// 16×16 LDS-tile transpose to keep VMEM coalesced in both directions.
// One workgroup per (tile_m, tile_n); 256 lanes per WG, 1 f32 per lane.
// LDS uses +1 stride padding (17×16) to avoid bank conflicts on read.
//
// Grid: ((M+15)/16) × ((N+15)/16) workgroups in 1-D grid_x; the kernel
// divides wg_id_x by num_tiles_n internally to recover (tile_m, tile_n).
